{"session_id": 45, "bill_id": 12681, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 150, "bill_title": "to revise certain provisions relating to a commercial driver's instruction permit and to clarify the issuance of a commercial driver's license work permit.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 1943, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1976, "is_prime": true}], "keywords": ["Commercial Trucking & Drivers", "Drivers' Licenses & Identification Cards", "Signed by Governor"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 12681, "bill_version_id": 73723, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1997-01-28T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to revise certain provisions relating to a commercial driver's instruction permit and to clarify the issuance of a commercial driver's license work permit. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 32-12-82 be amended to read as follows: 32-12-82. Unless driving under a commercial driver's instruction permit or a valid Class 1 or Class 2 license and accompanied by the holder of a commercial driver's license valid for the vehicle being driven, no No person may drive a commercial motor vehicle on the highways of this state unless the person holds and has in his immediate possession a commercial driver's license with applicable endorsements valid for the vehicle he the person is driving or is driving under a commercial driver's instruction permit . A violation of this section is a Class 2 misdemeanor. Section 2. That \u00a7 32-12-117 be amended to read as follows: 32-12-117. If a person's driver's license or privilege to drive has been suspended or revoked for a violation committed while driving a noncommercial vehicle and the court issues an order permitting the person to operate a motor vehicle for purposes of the person's employment, the department shall, at the request of the court, issue a commercial driver license driver's work permit to be used by the person to drive a commercial motor vehicle only for employment purposes during the period of suspension or revocation. The fee for such a license work permit is fifteen dollars. However, no commercial driver license driver's work permit may be issued pursuant to this section to any person if that person's driver's license or privilege to drive has been suspended or revoked for a second or subsequent time within three years prior to the three year period immediately preceding the current violation. No commercial driver license driver's work permit may be issued pursuant to this section to a school bus driver. If a person operating with a commercial driver license for employment purposes only driver's work permit is convicted of a moving traffic violation or is found to be in violation of restrictions imposed by the license work permit , the person's license work permit may be canceled and the person may is not be eligible for another license permit during the current suspension or revocation period."}, {"bill_id": 12681, "bill_version_id": 73722, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "1997-02-25T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 12681, "action_date": "1997-01-28T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 72887, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/72887.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 191, "committee_id_action": 545, "committee_id_assigned": 529, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 12681, "action_date": "1997-02-04T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 72277, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/72277.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 529, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 12681, "action_date": "1997-02-04T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 72277, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature